## Quantitative Summary of Personality Trait Changes Across the Lifespan

| Trait           | General Pattern of Change Over Lifespan                         | Notable Sex Differences                  | Magnitude of Change             |
|-----------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------|--------------------------------|
| **Neuroticism** | Declines through adulthood; increases in older age (U-shaped)   | Women show steeper declines than men    | Small to moderate              |
| **Extraversion**| Declines steadily, especially social vitality facet             | Minimal sex differences                  | Small to moderate              |
| **Openness**    | Increases in adolescence, stable in middle adulthood, declines in old age | Minimal sex differences           | Small to moderate              |
| **Agreeableness**| Generally increases throughout adulthood, especially in old age| Minimal sex differences                  | Small                        |
| **Conscientiousness**| Increases through early and middle adulthood, declines after 60 | Minimal sex differences                  | Small to moderate              |

*Data synthesized from Roberts et al. (2006), Srivastava et al. (2003), and Graham et al. (2020).*

